        { "id": "s4-chart", "type": "tikz", "content": "\\begin{tikzpicture}\n\\path (0,0) rectangle (0.01,0.01);\n\\begin{axis}[\n  width=10cm, height=6cm,\n  xlabel={\\small Year}, ylabel={\\small CPI YoY (\\%)},\n  xmin=2017.5, xmax=2024.5, ymin=0, ymax=10,\n  xtick={2018,2019,2020,2021,2022,2023,2024},\n  grid=major, grid style={gray!20},\n  tick label style={font=\\scriptsize}, label style={font=\\scriptsize},\n  axis lines=left, every axis plot/.append style={thick}\n]\n\\addplot[color=teal!70!black, dashed, thick] coordinates {(2017.5,2) (2024.5,2)};\n\\node[font=\\scriptsize, text=teal!70!black, anchor=west] at (axis cs:2023.2,2.4) {2\\% Fed target};\n\\addplot[color=orange!80!black, mark=*, mark size=2pt] coordinates {(2018,2.4) (2019,1.8) (2020,1.2) (2021,4.7) (2022,8.0) (2023,4.1) (2024,3.0)};\n\\node[font=\\scriptsize, orange!80!black, anchor=south] at (axis cs:2022,8.2) {8.0\\% peak};\n\\end{axis}\n\\end{tikzpicture}", "position": { "x": 60, "y": 155 }, "size": { "w": 480, "h": 235 }, "style": { "backgroundColor": "#FDF4E3" } },
        { "id": "s4-side-tag", "type": "text", "content": "WHAT IT MEASURES", "position": { "x": 570, "y": 135 }, "size": { "w": 330, "h": 14 }, "style": { "fontSize": 10, "color": "#FF6B35" } },
        { "id": "s4-side-rule", "type": "shape", "shape": "rectangle", "position": { "x": 570, "y": 153 }, "size": { "w": 330, "h": 1 }, "style": { "fill": "#0A2540", "stroke": "#0A2540", "strokeWidth": 0 } },
        { "id": "s4-side-b", "type": "text", "content": "$$ \\pi_t = \\frac{P_t - P_{t-1}}{P_{t-1}} $$\n\nThe CPI is a weighted basket: ~34% shelter, ~13% food, ~7% energy, rest services and durable goods.\n\n**Core CPI** strips volatile food & energy to show the persistent trend the Fed reacts to.", "position": { "x": 570, "y": 168 }, "size": { "w": 330, "h": 270 }, "style": { "fontSize": 12, "color": "#0A2540", "lineHeight": 1.6 } },
        { "id": "s4-bottom-tag", "type": "text", "content": "SHOCKS VS TRENDS", "position": { "x": 60, "y": 385 }, "size": { "w": 480, "h": 14 }, "style": { "fontSize": 10, "color": "#FF6B35" } },
        { "id": "s4-bottom-b", "type": "text", "content": "The 2021-22 spike blended pandemic-era supply shocks with loose monetary policy — disentangling the two is the active research question.", "position": { "x": 60, "y": 402 }, "size": { "w": 480, "h": 40 }, "style": { "fontSize": 11, "color": "#0A2540", "lineHeight": 1.5 } }
      ]
