        { "id": "s5-side-b", "type": "text", "content": "In the short run, lower unemployment pushes wages — and therefore prices — up. Central banks exploit this to steer demand: tightening when inflation runs hot, easing when the cycle cools.\n\nThe long-run curve is vertical at the NAIRU: you can trade inflation for unemployment only temporarily.", "position": { "x": 570, "y": 170 }, "size": { "w": 330, "h": 230 }, "style": { "fontSize": 12, "color": "#0A2540", "lineHeight": 1.6 } },
